---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Gaming Monitor Buying Guide",
  "description": "Comprehensive reference guide for choosing the right gaming monitor including panel types, refresh rates, resolution, and best monitors by budget.",
  "url": "https://leeroyjenkins.quest/guide-monitor-buying.html",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Leeroy Jenkins"
  }
};
---

<SiteLayout
  site="leeroyjenkins"
  title="Gaming Monitor Buying Guide | Leeroy Jenkins"
  description="Comprehensive reference guide for choosing the right gaming monitor including panel types, refresh rates, resolution, and best monitors by budget."
  canonical="https://leeroyjenkins.quest/guide-monitor-buying" schema={schema}
>
  <style>
:root {
      --bg: #08060e;
      --card-bg: #100e18;
      --border: #221e30;
      --accent: #9333EA;
      --accent-hover: #7e22ce;
      --text-primary: #d8d0e8;
      --text-secondary: #888;
      --font-ui: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      --font-mono: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    }

    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      font-family: var(--font-ui);
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      line-height: 1.6;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 60px 24px;
    }

    header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 40px;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: 900;
      letter-spacing: -1px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fff 0%, var(--accent) 100%);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }

    header p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    /* Search Bar */
    .search-container {
      margin-bottom: 40px;
      position: relative;
    }
    .search-input {
      width: 100%;
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 2px solid var(--border);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      padding: 16px 20px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      font-family: var(--font-ui);
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      outline: none;
      transition: border-color 0.2s;
    }
    .search-input:focus {
      border-color: var(--accent);
    }
    .search-input::placeholder {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
    }

    /* Cards & Layout */
    .section-card {
      background: var(--card-bg);
      border: 2px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
      box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
      transition: opacity 0.3s;
    }
    .section-card.hidden {
      display: none;
    }
    .section-card h2 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .grid-3 {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
      gap: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .info-box {
      background: var(--bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 20px;
      border-radius: 12px;
    }
    .info-box h3 {
      color: var(--accent);
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
    .info-box p, .info-box ul {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    .info-box ul {
      margin-left: 20px;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }
    .info-box li {
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    .val-pill {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      background: var(--border);
      color: #fff;
      padding: 4px 10px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      margin: 2px 4px 2px 0;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.1s;
      user-select: none;
    }
    .val-pill:hover {
      background: var(--accent);
    }
    .val-pill:active {
      transform: scale(0.95);
    }

    /* Table */
    .table-container {
      overflow-x: auto;
      margin-top: 20px;
      background: var(--bg);
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      text-align: left;
    }
    th, td {
      padding: 16px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    th {
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #fff;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
      white-space: nowrap;
    }
    td {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
    tr:last-child td {
      border-bottom: none;
    }
    .badge {
      font-family: var(--font-mono);
      background: var(--border);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      padding: 4px 8px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      display: inline-block;
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }

    /* Expandable details */
    details {
      background: var(--bg);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 12px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
    }
    summary {
      padding: 16px 20px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #fff;
      cursor: pointer;
      list-style: none;
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      user-select: none;
    }
    summary::-webkit-details-marker {
      display: none;
    }
    summary::after {
      content: '+';
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 400;
    }
    details[open] summary::after {
      content: '−';
    }
    .details-content {
      padding: 0 20px 20px 20px;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    /* SEO Section */
    .seo-content {
      margin-top: 60px;
    }
    .seo-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      color: #fff;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      margin-top: 40px;
    }
    .seo-content p {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .seo-content ul {
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      margin-left: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .seo-content li {
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    /* Footer */
    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 40px 24px;
      margin-top: 60px;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    footer a {
      color: var(--accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
      .section-card { padding: 24px; }
      .search-input { padding: 12px 16px; }
    }
  </style>

<div class="container">
    

    <div class="search-container">
      <input type="text" id="searchInput" class="search-input" placeholder="Search for IPS, 144Hz, 4K, response time...">
    </div>

    <div id="contentSections">
      <!-- Panel Types -->
      <div class="section-card" data-tags="panel types ips va tn oled colors contrast viewing angles">
        <h2>Panel Types</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h3>IPS (In-Plane Switching)</h3>
            <p>Best overall for most gamers.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Excellent color accuracy, great viewing angles, fast response times.</li>
              <li><strong>Cons:</strong> "IPS glow" in dark rooms, average contrast ratio (~1000:1).</li>
              <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Competitive gaming, content creation, general use.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box">
            <h3>VA (Vertical Alignment)</h3>
            <p>Best for deep blacks and contrast.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Pros:</strong> High contrast ratio (3000:1+), deep blacks, good colors.</li>
              <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Slower pixel response times (can cause smearing), narrower viewing angles.</li>
              <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Story-driven games, movie watching, dark room gaming.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box">
            <h3>TN (Twisted Nematic)</h3>
            <p>Best for extreme competitive gaming on a budget.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Extremely fast response times, high refresh rates at low cost.</li>
              <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Poor color reproduction, terrible viewing angles.</li>
              <li><strong>Best for:</strong> Hardcore CS2/Valorant players on a strict budget.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <details>
          <summary>What about OLED?</summary>
          <div class="details-content">
            <p>OLED (Organic Light-Emitting Diode) is the premium tier. It offers true blacks (infinite contrast) and near-instantaneous response times (<span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('0.03ms', this)">0.03ms</span>). The main drawbacks are high cost, lower peak brightness in bright rooms, and the potential risk of permanent burn-in from static HUDs over long periods.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>

      <!-- Refresh Rate -->
      <div class="section-card" data-tags="refresh rate hz fps 60hz 144hz 240hz 360hz smoothness">
        <h2>Refresh Rate (Hz)</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 20px;">Refresh rate is how many times per second the monitor updates with new images. Higher is smoother.</p>

        <div class="table-container">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Refresh Rate</th>
                <th>Experience Level</th>
                <th>Target Audience</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge">60Hz</span></td>
                <td>Standard</td>
                <td>Office work, casual console gaming. Not recommended for PC gaming.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge">144Hz - 165Hz</span></td>
                <td>Sweet Spot</td>
                <td>The new standard for PC gaming. Huge upgrade from 60Hz. Best balance of price and performance.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge">240Hz</span></td>
                <td>Competitive</td>
                <td>Serious multiplayer gamers (Valorant, Apex, CS2). Noticeably smoother than 144Hz.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><span class="badge">360Hz - 500Hz+</span></td>
                <td>Esports Pro</td>
                <td>Professional players where every millisecond counts. Requires extreme PC hardware.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Response Time -->
      <div class="section-card" data-tags="response time ms gtg mprt ghosting input lag">
        <h2>Response Time</h2>
        <div class="info-box" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
          <p>Response time measures how fast a pixel can change colors, usually from gray-to-gray (GtG). Slower response times cause <strong>ghosting</strong> or smearing behind fast-moving objects.</p>
        </div>
        <details>
          <summary>GtG vs MPRT: What's the difference?</summary>
          <div class="details-content">
            <p><strong>GtG (Gray-to-Gray):</strong> The true measurement of pixel transition speed. Look for 1ms GtG or lower for gaming.</p>
            <p style="margin-top: 8px;"><strong>MPRT (Moving Picture Response Time):</strong> Often used in marketing. It relies on backlight strobing to hide ghosting, which can lower brightness and cause eye strain. GtG is the more important metric.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <div style="margin-top: 16px;">
          <strong style="color: var(--text-primary);">Ideal Values: </strong>
          <span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('1ms GtG', this)">1ms GtG</span>
          <span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('0.5ms GtG', this)">0.5ms GtG</span>
          <span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('0.03ms', this)">0.03ms (OLED)</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Resolution -->
      <div class="section-card" data-tags="resolution 1080p fhd 1440p qhd 4k uhd ppi size 24 inch 27 inch 32 inch">
        <h2>Resolution & Size</h2>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="info-box">
            <h3>1080p (FHD)</h3>
            <p><span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('1920x1080', this)">1920x1080</span></p>
            <ul style="margin-top: 12px;">
              <li><strong>Ideal Size:</strong> 24 inches</li>
              <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Very easy to run at high FPS, cheap.</li>
              <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Looks pixelated on screens larger than 24".</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box">
            <h3>1440p (QHD)</h3>
            <p><span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('2560x1440', this)">2560x1440</span></p>
            <ul style="margin-top: 12px;">
              <li><strong>Ideal Size:</strong> 27 inches</li>
              <li><strong>Pros:</strong> The sweet spot. Sharp text, great detail, manageable performance cost.</li>
              <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Requires a mid-to-high tier GPU for high FPS.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="info-box">
            <h3>4K (UHD)</h3>
            <p><span class="val-pill" onclick="copyText('3840x2160', this)">3840x2160</span></p>
            <ul style="margin-top: 12px;">
              <li><strong>Ideal Size:</strong> 28 - 32 inches</li>
              <li><strong>Pros:</strong> Incredible detail and sharpness. Best for visual fidelity.</li>
              <li><strong>Cons:</strong> Very demanding on hardware. Expensive.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Best by Budget -->
      <div class="section-card" data-tags="best monitors budget picks tier list recommendations cheap premium">
        <h2>Best Monitors by Budget</h2>
        <div class="table-container">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Tier</th>
                <th>Target Specs</th>
                <th>Typical Use Case</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Budget</strong><br><span style="font-size: 0.85em; color: var(--text-secondary);">$100 - $180</span></td>
                <td><span class="badge">1080p</span> <span class="badge">IPS</span> <span class="badge">144Hz+</span></td>
                <td>Entry-level PC builds, competitive gaming on a budget.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Mid-Range</strong><br><span style="font-size: 0.85em; color: var(--text-secondary);">$250 - $400</span></td>
                <td><span class="badge">1440p</span> <span class="badge">IPS</span> <span class="badge">165Hz+</span></td>
                <td>The majority of PC gamers. Perfect balance of looks and speed.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>High-End</strong><br><span style="font-size: 0.85em; color: var(--text-secondary);">$600 - $900</span></td>
                <td><span class="badge">4K 144Hz+</span> OR <span class="badge">1440p 360Hz</span></td>
                <td>High-end rigs (RTX 4070 Ti / RX 7900 XT or higher).</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Enthusiast</strong><br><span style="font-size: 0.85em; color: var(--text-secondary);">$900+</span></td>
                <td><span class="badge">OLED</span> <span class="badge">240Hz+</span></td>
                <td>Ultimate visual quality, infinite contrast, instant response.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="seo-content">
      <h2>How to choose a gaming monitor?</h2>
      <p>Choosing a gaming monitor comes down to balancing your budget against your PC's capabilities and the types of games you play. If you primarily play fast-paced esports titles like Valorant or Counter-Strike, prioritize high refresh rates (240Hz+) and low response times over resolution, often settling for a 1080p or 1440p IPS panel.</p>
      <p>If you prefer visually stunning single-player games like Cyberpunk 2077 or Red Dead Redemption 2, prioritize a higher resolution (1440p or 4K) and better contrast ratios (VA or OLED panels) to maximize visual immersion, even if it means sticking to a 144Hz refresh rate.</p>

      <h2>What is G-Sync and FreeSync?</h2>
      <p>G-Sync (Nvidia) and FreeSync (AMD) are variable refresh rate (VRR) technologies. They sync your monitor's refresh rate to the exact frame rate outputting from your graphics card. This eliminates screen tearing (when the monitor displays parts of two different frames at once) and reduces stuttering when your FPS fluctuates. Most modern monitors support FreeSync, and many are "G-Sync Compatible," meaning they work seamlessly with Nvidia GPUs as well.</p>

      <h2>Curved vs Flat Monitors</h2>
      <p>Curved monitors are designed to fill your peripheral vision and increase immersion, which is especially noticeable on ultrawide monitors (21:9 aspect ratio) or large 32-inch displays. The curvature is measured in 'R' (e.g., 1500R, 1800R), with a lower number meaning a tighter curve. For standard 16:9 displays under 27 inches, a flat panel is generally preferred for less distortion and better straight-on viewing.</p>
    </div>

    
  </div>
  <script is:inline>
// Search functionality
    const searchInput = document.getElementById('searchInput');
    const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.section-card');

    searchInput.addEventListener('input', (e) => {
      const term = e.target.value.toLowerCase();

      sections.forEach(section => {
        const tags = section.getAttribute('data-tags').toLowerCase();
        const text = section.innerText.toLowerCase();

        if (tags.includes(term) || text.includes(term)) {
          section.classList.remove('hidden');
        } else {
          section.classList.add('hidden');
        }
      });
    });

    // Copy utility for interactive pills
    function copyText(text, el) {
      navigator.clipboard.writeText(text).then(() => {
        if (el) {
          const originalText = el.innerText;
          el.innerText = 'Copied!';
          setTimeout(() => {
            el.innerText = originalText;
          }, 1500);
        }
      }).catch(err => {
        console.error('Failed to copy text: ', err);
      });
    }
  </script>
</SiteLayout>
